{
  "texts": [
    "• Steghofer et al. [99] believe that the next generation of STS should be based on AI technology.",
    "They emphasize dealing with the structure of adaptive next-generation intelligent systems, transitioning from the paradigm of the literate user to collaboration between the user and AI systems.",
    "• Dalpiaz [100] proposed an adaptive STS system architecture that enables self-reconstruction through a monitoring-diagnosis-coordination cycle.",
    "This architecture for self-reconfigurable STSs is based on goal-oriented requirements, considering the dynamic, unpredictable, and weakly controllable characteristics of STS in AI.",
    "Design principle Proposition Emerging sociotechnical characteristics of AI Human-centered characteristics Human-centered joint optimization Optimize both social and AI subsystems to empower human capabilities and enhance overall performance."
  ]
}